30/10/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romania took over the six-month rotating chairmanship of the Black Sea Economic Co-operation organisation (BSEC) from Moldova on Friday (28 October).
The handover occurred at the 13th meeting of the BSEC Council of Foreign Ministers, held in Chishinau.
Addressing the participants, Romania's Foreign Minister Mihai-Razvan Ungureanu said that enhancement of collaboration and strengthening of security in the region would be priorities for the Romanian chairmanship.
(Rompres - 28/10/05)
